  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison presumably wrote this letter to James Manning Winchell Yerrinton. Garrison writes: &quot;Please not to forget that the final hearing before the Committee on Capital Punishment will be had this afternoon, (probably at 3 o&apos;clock,) in the Hall of the House of Representatives. Pray, be &apos;in at the death,&apos; if you can. Yours, to hang the gallows.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The bottom of page one of this letter was cut off and William Lloyd Garrison&apos;s signature is missing.</subfield>
  </datafield>
